owd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b PG\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 Page 9\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LA\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 English\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 (c) 2008 The Financial Times Limited. All rights reserved \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The oil and gas sector has scarcely seemed a natural home for anyone with environmental leanings, at least until recently. But increasingly, new opportunities are opening within "green" niches in the sector.\par \par \uc2 They range from board-level posts taking responsibility for the company's environmental performance to more junior positions auditing a company's emissions, engineering roles looking after environmental technology, or posts on trading desks buying and selling carbon credits.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Anita Hoffmann, partner at \uc2 Heidrick &Struggles\uc2 , the headhunters, says: "We're seeing oil and gas companies look for chief sustainability officers, people who will drive the corporate strategic agenda."\par \par \uc2 Oil and gas companies are coming under increasing pressure to improve their environmental performance. In Europe, for instance, the sector is covered by the European Union's emissions trading scheme. This means limits are placed on the amount of carbon dioxide such companies can produce, and the companies can trade their quota with one another if they need to produce more. The constraints of this system have opened up new roles in emissions trading and jobs for engineers skilled in monitoring emissions, as well as opportunities for companies to cut their costs by employing energy efficiency experts to help reduce their emissions.\par \par \uc2 Environmental roles at the top of companies have also changed markedly in recent years, according to Ms Hoffmann. "It was very different a few years ago, when these positions were all about public affairs," she says. The \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  was seen as an aspect of \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 , falling within the PR department's function. But today, she says: "It's clearly a strategic issue" and so has been taken into the company's core operations.\par \par \uc2 The alternative energy sector is also growing fast - leading to a shortage of staff, according to a recent study by New Energy Finance, a clean energy market research company, and \uc2 Heidrick &Struggles.\uc2  Investment in clean energy worldwide in 2007 reached Dollars 148.4bn, up 60 per cent on the previous year, leading to a wealth of job openings. But in a survey of 75 business leaders in the sector, the companies found 37 per cent of respondents viewed the challenge of recruiting qualified staff as "very serious", with a further 59 per cent describing it as "moderately serious". Only 4 per cent said it was "not serious".\par \par \uc2 The hardest posts to fill, according to the poll, were those of chief technical officer, chief executive and senior project managers.\par \par \uc2 Michael Liebreich, chairman and chief executive of New Energy Finance, says: "Very rapid growth in investment in clean energy is putting a strain on the availability of senior managers with sector experience. There is strong momentum behind the growth of clean energy worldwide, with new investment up nearly fivefold between 2004 and 2007, but this is creating shortages not just of components such as silicon and transport infrastructure such as crane ships for offshore wind (turbines), but also of human capital."\par \par \uc2 Ms Hoffmann says the scale of the shortage "threatens to hamper the growth of this important industry".\par \par \uc2 But the skills shortage tells only half of the story. There are also many willing recruits trying to break into the alternative energy sector, and into green jobs in the oil and gas sectors, recruiters report.\par \par \uc2 "There is a huge amount of interest in environmental jobs," says Claire Skinner, managing director at Ruston WHEB, an executive search agency specialising in clean technology. Although the company specialises in senior posts, she says she receives approaches daily from newly qualified graduates.\par \par \uc2 For senior managers with positions reporting to the board, the rewards can be high, says Ms Skinner. In the US, she estimates salaries are higher than Dollars 300,000 a year basic, while in London they are generally between Pounds 120,000 and Pounds 150,000 for such posts, though they can reach around Pounds 180,000.\par \par \uc2 Candidates for such posts need three sets of skills, Ms Skinner says: technical skills, usually as an engineer or other hands-on experience of operating assets; commercial awareness, and an ability to understand the whole business; and communications skills, in being able to explain green issues and why they matter to the rest of the business and the outside world.\par \par \uc2 Jeremy Leggett started his career in the oil industry before making an unusual move into environmental activism and then to the alternative energy sector, where he founded and is now executive chairman of Solar Century, a solar technology company. He says of his transition: "Personally, I felt like I'd escaped a moral quagmire and found a massively fulfilling life mission all at once. That said, the last thing we need is brilliant people leaving the oil and gas industry en masse. Most have to stay and be brilliant in manning the fossil-fuel pumps while collectively we engineer the great retreat to renewables, otherwise the whole energy train is going to come off the tracks, and civilisation likely with it."\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\t