\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Companies are reshaping our society. It is not a new phenomenon, but the scope and speed of their impact are faster than ever. In 19th-century England, canal builders and railway engineers recast the demographic landscape, facilitating industrialisation, connecting faraway places and enabling ideas to travel too.\par \par \uc2 In the 20th century, airlines took up the baton, carrying goods, people, ideas and diseases further afield. Today, the most obvious shifts relate to electronic communications technology.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Think of how YouTube and \uc2 Google\uc2  are changing the behaviour of Generation Y and many of their parents, and of the anthropologists hired by \uc2 Nokia\uc2  and \uc2 Microsoft\uc2  in the search to understand why a tradesman, connected by mobile phone to a third party, may walk into your office giving little more than a raised eyebrow as a greeting.\par \par \uc2 Yet these are changes wrought by companies through their ability to adopt and spread technology in the search for profit.\par \par \uc2 The Corporate Responsibility Index established by Business in the Community is designed to do something much more deliberate: to spread best practice in the way companies interact with their stakeholders. It sounds innocuous enough, and would be hard to object to. Yet its impact on society may be just as great as, although less evident than, the revolution engendered by the information technology giants.\par \par \uc2 Since 2002, when it was launched, 280 of the largest companies in Britain have measured themselves via the index. It is in essence no more than a benchmarking tool that allows companies to assess their performance on \b \highlight22\uc2 Corporate Social Responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 , discover their strengths and weaknesses, and compare themselves to peers.\par \par \uc2 Yet signing up to indexation is a public statement that participants accept large parts of the constantly-evolving CSR agenda. Over the past year alone, 126 companies participated. All but 12 per cent of companies completed the index for all their operations. Many of these companies are international.\par \par \uc2 What are the ideas rippling through the corporate sector and beyond? The \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  is one of the top concerns among individuals. Many companies are achieving admirable and innovative progress it tackling environmental problems, even as some individuals resist changing their personal behaviour.\par \par \uc2 But the really fascinating impact stems from seemingly mundane measures that, at first sight, arguably do little more than remind companies of their legal responsibilities in the workplace and their markets.\par \par \uc2 The workplace indices measure performance on a wide range of issues, from equal opportunities and diversity through recruitment and skills training to health and safety. By measuring and benchmarking, companies discover how they are doing, and management takes responsibility.\par \par \uc2 Managers start to tackle shortcomings, and ponder how to do better. The commitments become embedded in corporate practice, in a way that an occasional industrial tribunal hearing for wrongful dismissal, or prosecution for health and safety negligence can never achieve.\par \par \uc2 As corporate attitudes change, so do those of employees, both within the workplace, where many spend half their waking hours five days a week, and without. Employees do not have one set of values in the workplace, and a second in their leisure time.\par \par \uc2 The obligation of equality at work is becoming a habit of equality in society at large. And Britain is a better place for it. Casual remarks, which might once have caused offence and a shake of the head, are no longer tolerated in society at large.\par \par \uc2 New attitudes to employees and skills have gelled happily with tighter labour-market conditions to trigger a virtuous spiral in apprenticeships, on-the-job training, and corporate education.\par \par \uc2 Companies have discovered that positive attitudes to skills development build staff loyalty and corporate reputation, as well as productivity. Although many still have far to go.\par \par \uc2 This bridges into the marketplace. Ethical business practices attract customers. Jo Warburton, of Co-operative Financial Services, winner of this year's Company Award, observes that the market for "ethical" financial products is growing at three times the rate of that for plain vanilla insurance and banking.\par \par \uc2 Pureprint, this year's Small Company Award winner, renamed itself to help signal its commitment to CSR values, differentiating itself from its peers, and giving itself a unique selling point.\par \par \uc2 Here too, there is a virtuous spiral. In competitive markets, companies that customers trust, and that align with their values, win advantage. But that interaction changes customers too.\par \par \uc2 Many of Pureprint's customers say they have become more environmentally aware since they began buying from a "green" supplier.\par \par \uc2 Corporate CSR policies are changing society. By offering carbon-offset options, companies make it possible for consumers to change their behaviour. With one mouse-click, an airline customer can fund a tree-planting scheme. By offering choice in their aisles, supermarkets enable customers to express their personal ethics in buying decisions.\par \par \uc2 But caveat vendor. The bar for CSR performance is constantly rising.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20080707_18128_398.xml\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ccsr : \uc2 Corporate Social Responsibility | ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nfact : \uc2 Factiva Filters | nfcpex : \uc2 FC&E Executive News Filter\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar