vironmentally-friendly Obama administration coming to power, a new green business coalition -- led by \uc2 Nike\uc2 , \uc2 Starbucks\uc2 , \uc2 Levi Strauss\uc2 , \uc2 Sun Microsystems\uc2  and Timberland -- is calling for stronger policies to slash global warming and to create a clean- energy economy.\par \par \uc2 The coalition called BICEP, or Business for Innovative Climate and Energy Policy, includes consumer-product companies involved for years in business and environmental issues.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 BICEP officials say retailers, their supply chains and the larger economy will be hurt by global warming's potential effects.\par \par \uc2 So BICEP is proposing more aggressive policies for:\par \par \uc2 *Greenhouse gases. Tougher federal targets for greenhouse gas reduction, including 25% by 2020 and 80% by 2050.\par \par \uc2 *Renewable energy. Federal regulations requiring that 20% of electricity come from renewable energy sources such as wind and solar by 2020, and 30% by 2030.\par \par \uc2 *Coal-fired plants. Federal laws limiting the building of new coal-fired power plants that do not capture carbon emissions.\par \par \uc2 Mindy Lubber, president of Ceres, a coalition of environmental groups and large investors managing $7 trillion in assets, says she expects to see legislation using BICEP proposals. Lubber, a former Environmental Protection Agency official, says lawmakers need to hear that green energy "can be good for the economy."\par \par \uc2 According to the United Nations \b \h