bl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 In a serious recession companies tend to batten down the hatches and go for short-term priorities.\par \par \uc2 A consequence of this is that issues such as sustainability can be put aside and viewed as useful but inessential disciplines.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 That is the clich\u233\'00\'E9. But in the current downturn, there are signs that this is not necessarily the case.\par \par \uc2 "I don't see any greater downturn in this space than any other space," says Chris Tuppen, chief sustainability officer at BT. If anything, sustainability disciplines prove helpful in a downturn.\par \par \uc2 "In tough times, when people want to lower costs, cutting energy activities delivers both cost savings and carbon reduction. There is a mutual reinforcing," he says.\par \par \uc2 Jan Babiak, global climate change and sustainability leader at accounting firm Ernst & Young, agrees. "Where you narrow your carbon footprint, you will find low-hanging fruit and savings," she says.\par \par \uc2 The differentiating factor will lie in how far companies got to grips with sustainability before the downturn.\par \par \uc2 If a company has built sustainability into its main structures, it will derive benefits during a recession. But companies that failed to do so will lose out.\par \par \uc2 "Where companies have made the link between the idea that 'this is a good thing' and 'we will have a competitive advantage', then sales will rise or they can reduce costs," says Richard Reid, chairman of KPMG London.\par \par \uc2 "However, where companies saw it as merely 'a good thing', then they may not persevere."\par \par \uc2 It is all a question of to what extent companies can see benefits and have created systems to measure them with. "Where people can save money or increase revenue, they will continue to do so," says Mr Reid.\par \par \uc2 "A lot of companies are pushing forward with the sustainability agenda," he explains.\par \par \uc2 "Rolls-Royce, for example, sees fuel burn as crucial. It is a question of how much fuel is used at so many revs. It is important to be as efficient as possible because of both costs and the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he says. "Where that link exists in a company the work will continue."\par \par \uc2 Malcolm Preston, the recently appointed chief executive of the sustainability practice at PwC, detects a sea-change. "In the past, this was more peripheral to enterprises," he says. "But boards of directors are now taking a bigger interest. It is becoming business-critical and mainstream."\par \par \uc2 The value to a company of integrating sustainability efforts with mainstream accounting is obvious.\par \par \uc2 At a recent forum held by the Prince of Wales Accounting for Sustainability project, Philip Scott, group chief financial officer at insurance company Aviva, and Louella Eastman, group \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  (CSR) director, extolled the benefits of sustainability and finance people working together.\par \par \uc2 For them, the real value started to flow through the company when the financial team and the CSR team could formally exchange thoughts.\par \par \uc2 However, it was also a significant moment when sustainability information became inextricably linked with financial data and therefore started to have strategic import.\par \par \uc2 "It brings more focus on sustainability as a cost-driver," says Ms Eastman. "It is as important to the business as financial data and becomes more visible around the company."\par \par \uc2 Her views were echoed at the same forum by Bob Laux, director of technical reporting and accounting at Microsoft.\par \par \uc2 He warned of the dangers of separate silos of information in a corporate structure. "Energy efficiency is a datacentre," he said. "You need to integrate it in your strategy." This is part of the danger in a downturn. "It is a real test as to how integrated it is into the business," says Mr Tuppen.\par \par \uc2 "Companies that have recently come into managing this will not have it properly embedded in the business and are more likely to slip away than those companies where it is fully integrated. Businesses may not recognise the connection if it is not fully integrated."\par \par \uc2 Mr Reid at KPMG agrees. "The key issue is companies linking the sustainability agenda with the commercial agenda," he says.\par \par \uc2 "Those organisations that have built sustainability into their structure properly will come out of this better than those who saw it as a public relations measure," says Richard Spencer, manager, corporate responsibility at the Institute of Chartered Accountants in England and Wales, (ICAEW).\par \par \uc2 In part it is now up to the accountants to reinforce the message.\par \par \uc2 "The accountancy professions round the world can make a huge difference," says Paul Druckman, chairman of the executive board of the Prince's Accounting for Sustainability project and a past president of the ICAEW.\par \par \uc2 "We need to be advising businesses. We need to be advising chief financial officers." It is becoming a global effort.\par \par \uc2 Last month, the Federation of European Accountants (FEE), announced in a series of reports on sustainability that "the accountancy profession should be, and increasingly is, developing connected reporting models which link financial and non-financial metrics".\par \par \uc2 Within the Prince's Accounting for Sustainability project, a network of bodies from Australia to the US has been created to exchange information, experience and best practice.\par \par \uc2 The downturn may be creating a whole range of short-term issues for companies. But the long-term issues will dictate who survives.\par \par \uc2 Robert Bruce is a member of the executive board of the Prince's Accounting for Sustainability Project\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20090204_5845_396.xml\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ccsr : \uc2 Corporate Social Responsibility | cbestp : \uc2 Best Practice | ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nfact : \uc2 Factiv