d\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 (Copyright (c) 2009, Dow Jones & Company, Inc.) \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Several banks have cut back their analysis of companies' policies governing social responsibility, according to Thomson Reuters, which does a regular survey of equity analysts.\par \par \uc2 The cuts suggest investors who place a high priority on \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  may have to make do with less information on the subject, which can cover areas such as the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , human rights and consumer protection. However, investor representatives said they were seeing a "mixed picture" in banks' support of socially responsible investing.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Steve Kelly, global head of surveys at Thomson Reuters Extel, said \uc2 Citigroup Inc\uc2 ., \uc2 J.P. Morgan Chase &Co\uc2 . and \uc2 Bank of America\uc2 Merrill Lynch\uc2 , a unit of \uc2 Bank of America Corp\uc2 ., were among the banks that cut back in the past few months. \uc2 Merrill Lynch\uc2 's specialist, Zoe Knight, was one of about 20 analysts to leave the bank in January as a result of the merger with \uc2 Bank of America\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Representatives for \uc2 Citigroup\uc2  and \uc2 Merrill Lynch\uc2  said their banks weren't necessarily playing down the idea of socially responsible investment. Despite some cuts, both banks said they have employees working on socially responsible investment. \uc2 J.P. Morgan\uc2  didn't comment.\par \par \uc2 Mr. Kelly said the picture was not one of universal retreat. "Other banks, such as \uc2 HSBC\uc2 , have come to market recently with socially responsible analysis," he said.\par \par \uc2 Deutsche Bank AG\uc2  is making much of its climate-change team. Kevin Parker, \uc2 Deutsche Bank\uc2 's head of asset management, is backing a campaign that kicks off in New York next week to raise public awareness of the issue.\par \par \uc2 "Clearly, earlier this year some of the banks were making cuts across the board, and as part of that some of them changed their approach to SRI analysis," said Penny Green, chief executive of the U.K. Social Investment Forum. "There were some SRI analysts who left in the general cuts, but we believe that other areas and sectors were hit harder. The cuts to SRI were not disproportionate."\par \par \uc2 Sarah Wilson, chief executive of shareholder adviser Manifest, said she is more concerned about the impact of the financial crisis on responsible investing and good corporate governance. The cuts to corporate-governance teams come at a time when many are calling for more engagement, she said.\par \par \uc2 "There is a need for a lot more thought in relation to companies and voting at annual general meetings," she said. "Just voting on its own is meaningless, the governance and the investment teams need to work together on it in a more joined-up way. But with cutbacks on core spending, governance is seen as a nice to have, not a need to have."\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.djreprints.com/link/DJRFactiva.html?FACTIVA=weco20090611000040"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 License this article from Dow Jones Reprint Service}}}\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 cnyc : \uc2 JPMorgan Chase & Co. | ncnbco : \uc2 Bank of America Corporation | ccred : \uc2 Citigroup Inc. | deut : \uc2 Deutsche Bank AG\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ifinal : \uc2 Financials | ibnk : \uc2 Banking/Credit | i814 : \uc2 Banking | i81402 : \uc2 Commercial Banking\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clp