it back on again."\par \par \uc2 Maintaining the commitment to \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  has helped companies keep up employee morale, business values and their brand and reputation, "which is critical in this \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Mr. Salzberg said.\par \par \uc2 Almost half of the companies surveyed by the Conference Board in February reduced 2009 giving budgets as a result of inadequate financial resources and declines in corporate foundation endowments.\par \par \uc2 Others, including Deloitte, continue to give the same amount, but have shifted their approach to get more strategic: The company now doles out funds primarily to non-profit groups to whom it already offers free consulting services. Deloitte has committed $50 million over three years to pro bono projects and plans to launch a fellowship program to sponsor 10 managers to spend three to six months working for a non-profit group.\par \par \uc2 The firm emphasizes employee performance when working on pro bono accounts. It "is considered just as important to your career as other assignments," Mr. Salzberg said.\par \par \uc2 Deloitte looks to fund organizations with projects that can be replicated and have a proven track record of getting things done, said Evan Hochberg, national director of community involvement at Deloitte.\par \par \uc2 The company is narrowing its philanthropic focus to address problems of education, particularly college and work-force readiness, and is planning to take a public stand on social-policy issues.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.djreprints.com/link/DJRFactiva.html?FACTIVA=wjco20090729000030"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 License this article from Dow Jones Reprint Service}}}\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\tr